          <p>The Helen Martindale Roberts series contains an itemized index of collection materials and a DVD with over 100 images of collection artifacts catalogued by Roberts in 2012. Additionally, the series contains business records and professional transactions, including insurance documents, bills of sale, permits, deeds, partnership agreements and notary public certifications from a period between1852-1877. There are also numerous letters between M. J. Bialey (pronounced Beely), H.D. Braddock and Co., and members of the Ingraham family on scattered dates from1863-1881.</p>
